After JIRA installation- open JIRA Url on the browser and follow the steps below to set up the first time use.
Following link contains the several database setup instruction with Jira
https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/database-configuration-159764.html
Install PostgreSQL
Step1: After JIRA installation- open JIRA Url on the browser and follow the steps below to set up the first time use.
Choose-  I'll setup myself 
Step2: Select Next
At Database setup page - Choose My own database and fill the required detail to access the database.
https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/database-setup-for-postgresql-173244522.html
 a: Database type: PostgreSQL
 b: Hostname: localhost
 c: Port: 5432
 d: Database: Jira
 e: username: postgres
 f: Password: ********
 g: Scehma: Public
 
 
MS SQL default port: 3306
Microsoft SQL server default port: 1433
Oracle default port: 1521
PosgreSQL default port: 5432
